33 jurors summoned; appeared; sworn.  20 seated for voir dire.  12 sworn to hear the case.

9:12am  Defendant Matthew J. Cypcar in court with Attorney Jennifer Amelia Cunha.  ADA Troy D Cross appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Preliminary jury instructions reviewed. 9:20 Jury entered courtroom; Court instructed jurors; jurors sworn; 20 seated.  Voir dire; peremptory strikes; 12 jurors selected; sworn. Court in recess. 10:15/10:28  Court resumed; appearances the same.  Atty Cunha addressed Amended Complaint; Court denied Atty Cunha's motion.  Atty Cunha addressed evidence; Court denied motion.  Atty Cunha requested evidentiary hearing; Court granted.  State called Sergeant Matthew Menard, Columbia County Sheriff's Office, sworn, testimony taken, Court ruled statements are admissible.  10:44 Jury returned; Court reviewed instructions with jurors, 10:59 Opening statements by counsel.  11:05 State called witness Sergeant Matthew Menard, Columbia County Sheriff's Office, sworn.  Direct exam; Exhibits #1 and #2 marked, offered and received.  11:17 Jurors excused; Court in recess. 11:37  Court resumed, appearances the same.  Court addressed audio issues.  Atty Cunha objected to analyst; Court proceeded w/Daubert Hearing.  Court excused jury at 11:44.  State called witness Analyst Kenneth Olson, State Crime Lab, sworn; testimony taken 12:03pm Witness excused.  Atty Cunha objected to analyst testifying; Atty Cunha's motion was denied.  Court in recess until 1:00.  1:08 Court resumed; appearances the same; jury returned.  Cross exam of Deputy Menard by Atty Cunha; Atty Cunha played audio of stop.  1:26  Redirect, recross, witness excused.  1:32  State called Deputy Nicholas Willman, Columbia County Sheriff's Office, sworn.  Direct exam; cross exam; redirect, witness excused.  1:41 State called Analyst Kenneth Olson of the State Crime Lab, sworn.  1:42  Direct exam; cross exam; witness excused.  1:59  State rested; jury excused.  Court reviewed with defendant the right to testify, defendant will not testify.  Atty Cunha moved for a Not Guilty verdict, State objected, Court denied motion.  Atty Cunha requested leave to call rebuttal witness; Court in recess at 2:00/2:19 Court resumed; appearances the same.  Court denied request for rebuttal witness, Court reviewed jury instructions with counsel.  Recess at 2:34/2:45 Court resumed; appearances the same; Jury returned, Defense rested.  Court instructs jurors.  3:04 Closing arguments by counsel, 3:10 Court recites final instructions to jury; bailiffs sworn; jurors excused for deliberation.  Court in recess 3:15/4:35  Court resumed; appearances the same; question from jury discussed;  jury returned to courtroom; jury instruction read; jury removed to deliberate. Court in recess. 4:38/4:40 Court resumed; appearances the same.  Question from jury; answered in writing.  Court in recess 4:42/5:18 Court resumed; appearances the same; jury returned.  Verdict:  Count 1 - Guilty, Count 2 - Guilty.  Jurors polled individually; Court accepted verdict.  Court released jurors; sentencing to be set; Court adjourned at 5:20
